      "side": 1,
      "message": "What you propose is isomorphic to what I have, except I\u0027ll (probably) need to reverse direction of traversal in \u0027targets()\u0027 from .children() to .parents().\n\nIt\u0027s like multiplying negative numbers. If I reverse a direction of an edge in one place, I need to have a reversal somewhere else too to keep same logic.\n\nI started with the mental model of how I imagine the \u0027triggers\u0027 edge (and the traversal logic) should look like and arrived to the necessity to have \u0027poller\u0027 ---owns---\u003e \u0027triggerrer\u0027 ---triggers---\u003e \u0027builder_ref\u0027 ordering.\n\nIf we start with a requirement \u0027builder_ref\u0027 ---triggered_by--\u003e \u0027triggerer\u0027 ---owned_by---\u003e \u0027poller\u0027 we\u0027ll arrive to a traversal logic that may (or may not) look odd.\n\nI\u0027ll try it in the next patch set to see how it looks.",
